29
00:01:18,286 --> 00:01:21,539
Guys, I love it. How did you know my size?

30
00:01:22,248 --> 00:01:25,085
We got you an extra large
so we can enjoy it too.

31
00:01:26,753 --> 00:01:28,296
Is this chair too small?

32
00:01:29,672 --> 00:01:31,758
Just give Leia our birthday card already.

33
00:01:32,258 --> 00:01:33,176
Inside cat.

34
00:01:33,259 --> 00:01:34,928
[gasps] Outside cat.

35
00:01:35,011 --> 00:01:37,764
Inside cat. Outside cat. Ins--

36
00:01:37,847 --> 00:01:38,681
No more cat.

37
00:01:39,224 --> 00:01:42,644
I missed you guys.
My sad hole was lonely without you.

38
00:01:43,728 --> 00:01:46,856
I'm not gonna let my breakup with Jay
ruin my birthday.

39
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:48,108
Not a breakup.

40
00:01:49,192 --> 00:01:50,193
Not a breakup.

41
00:01:51,194 --> 00:01:52,403
[both] Not a breakup.

42
00:01:53,321 --> 00:01:55,824
How many times
do you turn 15 in your life?

43
00:01:56,366 --> 00:01:57,367
Not that many.

44
00:01:58,827 --> 00:01:59,911
I'm over him.

45
00:01:59,994 --> 00:02:01,788
New year, new me.

46
00:02:02,580 --> 00:02:04,040
New Kids On The Block.

47
00:02:04,958 --> 00:02:06,251
I over-corrected.

48
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:10,213
What's this?
You spelled my name wrong on this card.

49
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:12,423
How do you not know
how to spell your girlfriend's name?

50
00:02:12,507 --> 00:02:13,842
Let me see that.

51
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:15,343
-[Nikki scoffs]
-[chuckles]

52
00:02:15,426 --> 00:02:16,427
Nik!

53
00:02:17,595 --> 00:02:19,764
People are leaving? I just got this right.

54
00:02:19,848 --> 00:02:21,683
-[rock music playing]
<i>-One, two, three, four!</i>

55
00:02:21,766 --> 00:02:23,768
<i>♪ Hangin' out down the street ♪</i>

56
00:02:23,852 --> 00:02:25,728
<i>♪ The same old thing we did last week ♪</i>

57
00:02:25,812 --> 00:02:27,939
<i>♪ Not a thing to do ♪</i>

58
00:02:28,022 --> 00:02:30,024
<i>♪ But talk to you ♪</i>

59
00:02:30,108 --> 00:02:31,401
<i>♪ We're all all right! ♪</i>

60
00:02:31,484 --> 00:02:32,735
<i>♪ We're all all right! ♪</i>

61
00:02:33,319 --> 00:02:35,363
[young woman] <i>Hello, Wisconsin!</i>

62
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:40,076
Well, Donna and Eric aren't gonna make it
for Leia's birthday.

63
00:02:41,077 --> 00:02:45,456
Eric's upset, but he knew the risks
when he signed up for Space Camp.

64
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:50,211
Kitty, he fell out of his bunk bed.
It's not exactly Apollo 13.

65
00:02:50,795 --> 00:02:53,464
Well, he is gonna wish
he slept on the bottom bunk

66
00:02:53,548 --> 00:02:58,303
because I am throwing
a classic Kitty Forman birthday bash.

67
00:03:01,139 --> 00:03:02,682
It's you and me, old friend.

68
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:04,809
We're about to put on a show.

69
00:03:05,476 --> 00:03:08,021
You're planning a kid's party.

70
00:03:08,104 --> 00:03:11,608
So let's try and not
get all stressed out this time.

71
00:03:11,691 --> 00:03:12,734
Don't worry.

72
00:03:12,817 --> 00:03:15,069
I woke up early to get a head start.

73
00:03:15,153 --> 00:03:18,948
Oh my God, it's 7:00 a.m.
I haven't deviled a damn thing!

74
00:03:20,825 --> 00:03:22,410
Well, I did my part.

75
00:03:22,493 --> 00:03:23,995
Took care of the gift.

76
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:26,164
Twenty dollars.

77
00:03:27,248 --> 00:03:29,500
-You did one thing. Good for you.
-[egg cracks]

78
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:35,173
I'm sorry. I snapped.
It's… Birthdays are fun.

79
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:36,674
[laughs]

80
00:03:36,758 --> 00:03:38,718
It's gonna be a long day.

81
00:03:39,761 --> 00:03:42,263
Hey there! Hi there! Ho there!

82
00:03:43,806 --> 00:03:45,934
And it just got longer.

83
00:03:46,434 --> 00:03:48,311
