-Oh.

251
00:12:43,971 --> 00:12:44,805
Well…

252
00:12:45,556 --> 00:12:47,266
He was driving me crazy, so I…

253
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:50,060
I put some cold medicine in his iced tea.

254
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:53,731
And some in his potato salad.

255
00:12:55,316 --> 00:12:56,817
Some more in his pudding.

256
00:12:58,068 --> 00:13:01,864
He just… He wouldn't go down, Red.
It was like… drugging a rhino.

257
00:13:03,491 --> 00:13:06,076
Anyhoo, he's fast asleep upstairs.

258
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,455
Wait till you see what I got Leia.

259
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:14,043
Bob went expensive, but I went thoughtful.

260
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:16,295
You sweet, sweet man.

261
00:13:17,546 --> 00:13:19,381
Her own cordless drill.

262
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:25,012
You stupid, stupid man.

263
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:29,141
But it's a great gift.
It gives her independence.

264
00:13:29,225 --> 00:13:33,145
She can fix things on her own.
Take care of herself.

265
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:37,066
Why are you looking at me like that?

266
00:13:38,108 --> 00:13:40,110
Did I not say it was cordless?

267
00:13:42,571 --> 00:13:45,366
Red, you need to think like a teenager.

268
00:13:45,449 --> 00:13:47,660
What did you want when you were 15?

269
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:49,495
A vaccine for polio.

270
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:53,165
All right. I'll keep looking.

271
00:13:53,249 --> 00:13:56,418
Man… I must have been really tired.

272
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:00,381
I fell asleep in the hallway.

273
00:14:01,507 --> 00:14:04,969
Well… you know,
that jet lag can be a killer.

274
00:14:06,095 --> 00:14:08,097
Let me get you some more iced tea.

275
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:12,184
[rock music playing]

276
00:14:14,603 --> 00:14:16,063
[Kitty] Ooh!

277
00:14:16,146 --> 00:14:18,566
Somebody brought their appetite.

278
00:14:18,649 --> 00:14:21,610
So which one of my hors d'oeuvres
do you like best?

279
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:24,238
This clam dip? Love!

280
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:27,825
Whoopsie.

281
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:34,373
Okay, I've figured out high heels.
You can let go now.

282
00:14:34,456 --> 00:14:36,250
So you're gonna stand here
and wait for Jay?

283
00:14:36,333 --> 00:14:39,753
Yeah. And when he gets here,
I'm gonna grab him and Kelly his face off.

284
00:14:39,837 --> 00:14:42,631
[dramatic rock guitar riff plays]

285
00:14:45,342 --> 00:14:46,760
This is so embarrassing.

286
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,850
I thought I could win back Jay,
but he didn't even care enough to show.

287
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:54,643
I get it.

288
00:14:55,144 --> 00:14:57,646
No one came to watch me
DJ at the Peach Pit.

289
00:14:58,147 --> 00:14:59,690
Not even Donna Martin.

290
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:00,649
It's the worst.

291
00:15:00,733 --> 00:15:03,694
What was she like? I mean, between scenes?

292
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:05,905
What do you mean, "scenes"?

293
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:08,741
Never mind.

294
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,411
Thank you for coming
to my birthday, David.

295
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,872
-You were always my favorite.
-I'll take it.

296
00:15:18,626 --> 00:15:20,419
Who are you talking to?

297
00:15:20,502 --> 00:15:21,837
Uh, David. Nobody.

298
00:15:23,255 --> 00:15:24,381
This is stupid.

299
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:26,383
I wasted my whole birthday
thinking about Jay,

300
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,968
and he's clearly moved on.

301
00:15:28,052 --> 00:15:29,178
I'm done being pathetic.

302
00:15:29,261 --> 00:15:30,179
Finally!

303
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,681
-[doorbell chimes]
-Move, he's here! Move, he's here!

304
00:15:34,725 --> 00:15:35,684
Grandpa Bob?

305
00:15:36,185 --> 00:15:38,604
You mean Grandpa Tom Jones.

306
00:15:39,813 --> 00:15:42,816
I'm here to sing your birthday song
on your birthday gift.

307
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,653
You're gonna sing?
In front of my friends? In that jacket?

308
00:15:45,736 --> 00:15:46,862
I'll be over here.

309
00:15:48,572 --> 00:15:49,740
Tom Jones?

310
00:15:50,240 --> 00:15:54,119
More like Tom groans
getting up from the couch. Am I right?

311
00:15:55,537 --> 00:15:56,830
I am right.

312
00:15:56,914 --> 00:15:58,832
[soft karaoke instrumental playing]

313
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,961
Wrong song, but, hey, the show must go on.

314
00:16:02,544 --> 00:16:06,799
I'd like to dedicate this song
to my beautiful granddaughter, Leia.

315
00:16:06,882 --> 00:16:08,175
This one's for you.

316
00:16:08,258 --> 00:16:09,426
Oh no.

317
00:16:09,927 --> 00:16:12,221
<i>♪ Close your eyes ♪</i>

318
00:16:12,304 --> 00:16:13,973
<i>♪ Make a wish ♪</i>

319
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:19,144
<i>♪ And blow out the candlelight ♪</i>

320
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,313
Hey, it worked out. It's a birthday song.

321
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:23,273
This is not a birthday song.

322
00:16:23,357 --> 00:16:24,900
We'll ride it out together.

323
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:27,569
<i>♪ I'll make love to you ♪</i>

324
00:16:27,653 --> 00:16:29,488
<i>♪ Like you want me to ♪</i>

325
00:16:30,114 --> 00:16:32,324
<i>♪ And I'll hold you tight ♪</i>

326
00:16:32,408 --> 00:16:35,411
<i>♪ Baby, all through the night… ♪</i>

327
00:16:35,494 --> 00:16:37,079
This is our song. [chuckles]

328
00:16:37,162 --> 00:16:38,497
[Bob continues singing]

329
00:16:38,580 --> 00:16:41,417
It was playing on the radio the first time
you let me touch your butt.

330
00:16:42,459 --> 00:16:43,961
Oh, you remembered!

331
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:49,258
♪ <i>And I will not let go</i>
<i>Till you tell me to ♪</i>

332
00:16:49,341 --> 00:16:50,509
Wanna get some air?

333
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,469
Oh God, yes.

334
00:16:52,553 --> 00:16:56,223
<i>♪ Girl, relax ♪</i>

335
00:16:56,306 --> 00:16:58,183
Bob. Nobody's relaxed.

336
00:17:01,061 --> 00:17:03,355
Seems like you might have had
a rough night, kiddo.

337
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:07,067
I've only been 15 for a day,
and so far I don't like it.

338
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:08,861
I mean, nothing's gone right.

339
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,738
It's like I don't know what I'm doing.

340
00:17:10,821 --> 00:17:11,822
Well,

341
00:17:12,823 --> 00:17:15,075
everything's not gonna go right.

342
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:17,911
Give yourself a break.
You're half dumbass.

343
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,207
It's just…

344
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:26,295
Everyone else seems to have it all
figured out and I'm just making it all up.

345
00:17:27,046 --> 00:17:29,631
Well, I hate to break it to you, kid,

346
00:17:29,715 --> 00:17:34,303
but we're all just making it up
as we go along.

347
00:17:35,262 --> 00:17:37,056
So don't be so hard on yourself.

348
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,141
Thanks, Grandpa.

349
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:42,394
Oh. Hey, wait.

350
00:17:42,895 --> 00:17:44,271
Don't you want your present?

351
00:17:45,230 --> 00:17:47,858
["Slow Ride" opening riff playing]

352
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:50,569
<i>♪ Slow ride… ♪</i>

353
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,948
A car? You got me a car?

354
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,784
It belonged to your father.

355
00:17:57,493 --> 00:18:01,288
Tomorrow, we'll get your learner's permit,
and I'll teach you how to drive. Okay?

356
00:18:01,955 --> 00:18:03,290
Thank you, Grandpa.

357
00:18:03,373 --> 00:18:05,250
This is the best present I've ever gotten.

358
00:18:05,334 --> 00:18:06,418
Oh…

359
00:18:07,002 --> 00:18:09,046
Be sure to say that to Grandpa Bob.

360
00:18:10,547 --> 00:18:12,257
Happy birthday, kiddo.

361
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:15,177
<i>-♪ Slow ridin' woman, you're so fine ♪</i>
-[song fades out]

362
00:18:15,260 --> 00:18:17,679
You gave her the Vista Cruiser?

363
00:18:18,847 --> 00:18:21,809
Man, you really creamed my jeans.

364
00:18:25,020 --> 00:18:28,190
Can't you even lose like a normal person?

365
00:18:29,316 --> 00:18:31,652
Now, Red, it wasn't a competition.

366
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:37,282
I wanted to do something nice for Leia.

367
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:40,953
You guys are lucky
to spend all this time with her.

368
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:45,666
I don't want her
to forget about her ol' Grandpa Bob.

369
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:46,834
Oh.

370
00:18:47,668 --> 00:18:48,585
Damn it.

371
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:51,296
You're a good man, Bob.

372
00:18:52,714 --> 00:18:55,092
Annoying as hell, but a good man.

373
00:18:55,759 --> 00:18:57,886
Leia is lucky to have you.

374
00:18:58,470 --> 00:19:00,597
You guys are makin' me emotional.

375
00:19:02,391 --> 00:19:04,059
And I never cry.

376
00:19:05,727 --> 00:19:07,813
Bob, you are welcome here anytime.

377
00:19:07,896 --> 00:19:09,106
[chuckles]

378
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,190
Ooh.

379
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:12,484
I gotta see a man about a clam. [chuckles]

380
00:19:15,779 --> 00:19:17,030
"Anytime"?

381
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,241
Red, he's family.

382
00:19:19,324 --> 00:19:20,701
[grumbles] Eric!

383
00:19:25,372 --> 00:19:26,248
[rapping on window]

384
00:19:28,458 --> 00:19:29,293
Jay?

385
00:19:31,503 --> 00:19:33,255
Hey. Mind if I come in?

386
00:19:33,338 --> 00:19:34,965
Okay, but the party's over.

387
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:38,844
[strains] Yeah. I'm sorry I missed it.

388
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,638
It just didn't feel right
to show up with Serena.

389
00:19:41,722 --> 00:19:43,640
I still don't know why I invited her.

390
00:19:44,141 --> 00:19:46,685
-I just wanted you to be there.
-I wanted to be there too.

391
00:19:47,269 --> 00:19:50,397
But… at least I can wish you
a happy birthday.

392
00:19:51,023 --> 00:19:53,192
You know? Before it's too late.

393
00:19:58,822 --> 00:20:00,741
Whoa. Where did that come from?

394
00:20:00,824 --> 00:20:02,868
I guess I'm just
making it up as I go along.

395
00:20:07,331 --> 00:20:09,833
-You need to break up with Serena.
-Serena who?

396
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:10,876
[Jay chuckles]

397
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:13,253
["The World I Know"
by Collective Soul playing]

398
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,215
Hey, you wanna go for a drive?

399
00:20:16,924 --> 00:20:18,091
Yeah, but I don't have a car.

400
00:20:18,175 --> 00:20:19,551
[laughs softly] Not a problem.

401
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:25,933
<i>♪ So I walk up on high… ♪</i>

402
00:20:26,016 --> 00:20:28,143
-Hey, we kissed.
-I know.

403
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,437
This is the best birthday.

404
00:20:32,481 --> 00:20:33,941
[siren wails]

405
00:20:36,151 --> 00:20:37,152
Just be cool.

406
00:20:37,236 --> 00:20:39,238
You mean, for the first time in my life?!

407
00:20:39,321 --> 00:20:41,490
<i>♪ While the tears roll down ♪</i>

408
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:44,660
<i>♪ 'Cause it's the world I know ♪</i>

409
00:20:45,244 --> 00:20:47,746
<i>♪ Oh, it's the world I know ♪</i>

410
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:51,750
[rock music playing]

